history.content:
168. You definitely should Phase I 168, in fact, it should be the first class you Phase I. CS 168 is a great class with Prof. Shenker (never took it, but I know many people who have, also I went to a few lectures).

He is an extremely clear and effective lecturer. Not to mention highly qualified - he sold his company for $1.2 billion, but you wouldn't know that from talking to him as he's a very down to earth person. The material is also very applicable to both industry and research - you really gain an in-depth understanding of computer networks. 

10/10 recommend.

children.subject: +1 one of my favorite classes in berkeley.

history.content: I was wondering which ones I should phase 1. I am aware that you can phase 1 up to 13.5 units and probably going to lock in 189 and C100 for sure, but I am having a trouble deciding between 168 and 120.
